<section id="summary">
  <div class="sec-label">Executive Summary</div>
  <h2>Reach has doubled — but that's not the whole story.</h2>
  <p class="lede">Teach At VUS achieved impressive reach growth in 2025 (+115.5%), but behind that number sits a series of warning signs: engagement per reach fell 92.7%, new followers dropped by nearly 20%, and the current content mix is allocating resources away from where the audience is actually responding.</p>
  <p>This report walks through five layers of analysis — channel overview, content format, content pillars, posting time patterns, and individual post-level evidence — to answer one question: <b>what is actually building VUS's employer brand in the eyes of candidates, and what is just generating good-looking numbers on a dashboard?</b></p>
  <div class="callout">Core finding: the Page already has three content formulas proven to work — <b>but they are running in isolation</b>, with no strategy connecting them into one coherent candidate journey.</div>
</section>

<section id="overview">
  <div class="sec-label">01 — Page Overview</div>
  <h2>Reach is climbing, but Engagement is flashing a warning</h2>
  <p>An overview of the 8 core metrics for the channel this period, compared with the prior period:</p>

  <div class="kpi-grid">
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Posts Published</div><div class="value">594</div><div class="delta down">▼ -8.3%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Total Views</div><div class="value">4.15M</div><div class="delta up">▲ +27.5%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Organic Reach</div><div class="value">2.19M</div><div class="delta up">▲ +115.5%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Views / Post</div><div class="value">6,985</div><div class="delta up">▲ +39.1%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">Reach / Post</div><div class="value">3,679</div><div class="delta up">▲ +135.1%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">New Followers</div><div class="value">6,774</div><div class="delta down">▼ -19.9%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">ERR</div><div class="value">2.64%</div><div class="delta down">▼ -92.7%</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="label">CTR</div><div class="value">0.81%</div><div class="delta up">▲ +60.3%</div></div>
  </div>

  <h3>Reading the numbers: Visibility is up, Resonance is down</h3>
  <p>Reach/Post rose 135.1% even as the number of posts fell 8.3% — a clear sign that per-post distribution efficiency has improved significantly. But <b style="color:var(--ink)">ERR fell 92.7%</b>, which is a serious signal: content is reaching more people, but isn't compelling enough to generate a reaction — not enough likes, shares, or comments to build real social proof for the employer brand.</p>
  <p>At the same time, New Followers fell 19.9% even as reach roughly doubled. The Page is reaching more people, but not convincing enough of them to actively follow — meaning the content isn't yet giving people a strong enough reason to "stay." The one bright spot is CTR, up 60.3%, suggesting a small segment of viewers is showing genuine intent worth nurturing further.</p>

  <div class="callout">The Page is winning on <b>visibility</b>, but not yet on <b>resonance</b>. For an Employer Branding objective, this is the gap that needs to close first.</div>
</section>

<section id="format">
  <div class="sec-label">02 — Content Format Analysis</div>
  <h2>Photo dominates distribution; Video is being used in the wrong role</h2>
  <p>Comparing the share of posts against 4 performance metrics — Reach, Engagement, Link Clicks, and Views — across each content format.</p>

  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Format</th><th class="num">% Posts</th><th class="num">% Reach</th><th class="num">% Engagement</th><th class="num">% Link Clicks</th><th class="num">% Views</th><th>Actual Role</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td class="name">Photos</td><td class="num">84.34%</td><td class="num">86.51%</td><td class="num">78.30%</td><td class="num">96.23%</td><td class="num">88.12%</td><td><span class="tag over">Distribution + Click</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td class="name">Videos</td><td class="num">12.96%</td><td class="num">10.65%</td><td class="num">17.15%</td><td class="num">3.26%</td><td class="num">8.64%</td><td><span class="tag flag">Engagement-only</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td class="name">Reels</td><td class="num">1.85%</td><td class="num">0.85%</td><td class="num">1.12%</td><td class="num">0.18%</td><td class="num">0.93%</td><td><span class="tag neutral">Under-tested</span></td></tr>
      <tr><td class="name">Text</td><td class="num">0.84%</td><td class="num">1.99%</td><td class="num">3.43%</td><td class="num">0.33%</td><td class="num">2.30%</td><td><span class="tag over">High engage/post</span></td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <div class="grid2">
    <div class="card"><h4>📷 Photo</h4><p style="font-size:14px;">Carries both the distribution and click-conversion role (96.23% of link clicks) — but engagement per post is lower than its post share. Photo drives people to the link, but doesn't stop them long enough to react emotionally.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>🎬 Video</h4><p style="font-size:14px;">Currently an <b>engagement champion being wasted as a reach tool</b>. Highest engagement per post (17.15% from 12.96% of posts), but only 3.26% of link clicks — video isn't yet being used for its real strength: emotional storytelling.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>📱 Reels</h4><p style="font-size:14px;">Only ~11 posts out of 594 — far too small a sample for any strategic conclusion. This format is currently neglected and needs a dedicated creative sprint (20–30 posts) before it can be properly evaluated.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>📝 Text</h4><p style="font-size:14px;">Highest engagement-per-post rate system-wide (3.43% from just 0.84% of posts), but it can't be scaled — and doesn't fit the visual storytelling language Employer Branding needs.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section id="pillar">
  <div class="sec-label">03 — Content Pillar Analysis</div>
  <h2>Life at VUS is under-invested; Vietnam &amp; Relocation underperforms across the board</h2>
  <p>Mapping each pillar onto the Employer Branding funnel (Awareness → Consideration → Conversion) to identify which pillars are playing the right role, and which need restructuring.</p>

  <div class="barchart">
    <div class="legend"><span><i style="background:var(--vus-blue)"></i>% of Posts</span><span><i style="background:var(--teal)"></i>% of Organic Reach</span></div>

    <div class="barrow"><div class="blabel">Teach at VUS</div><div class="bartrack"><div class="barfill posts" style="width:30.98%"></div></div><div class="bval">30.98%</div></div>
    <div class="barrow"><div class="blabel"></div><div class="bartrack"><div class="barfill reach" style="width:30%"></div></div><div class="bval">~30%</div></div>

    <div class="barrow"><div class="blabel">Life at VUS</div><div class="bartrack"><div class="barfill posts" style="width:16.84%"></div></div><div class="bval">16.84%</div></div>
