  <h3>ERR by month — a story of content quantity dilution</h3>
  <div class="divider-note"><b>Observation:</b> When post volume spikes sharply (Jan 122 → Feb 147), ERR drops just as sharply (Index 123 → 32) and doesn't recover proportionally when volume comes back down. The ERR peak in Jun–Jul (Index 57) coincides with a moderate, stable volume (~140 posts) — not the year's highest volume.</div>
  <p>This is a clear sign of <b style="color:var(--ink)">content quantity dilution</b> — when too much is posted in a short span, individual posts compete with each other in-feed, reducing audience response per post. For Employer Branding — where the quality of brand perception matters more than the frequency of appearance — this is an issue that needs to be addressed at the editorial-strategy level.</p>
