<section id="conclusion">
  <div class="sec-label">06 — Conclusions</div>
  <h2>The Page already has the raw material for a complete Employer Branding funnel — it just hasn't been assembled</h2>
  <p class="lede">Bringing together all five layers of analysis, three strategic conclusions stand out clearly:</p>

  <ul class="clean">
    <li><b style="color:var(--ink)">Reach and Resonance are moving in opposite directions.</b> The 115.5% reach growth is a genuine distribution achievement, but the 92.7% drop in ERR and the 19.9% decline in new followers show the content isn't yet converting that reach into real brand connection.</li>
    <li><b style="color:var(--ink)">Three winning content formulas have been identified by the data, but they're running in isolation:</b> Meme/Humor (Awareness) → Authentic raw video (Trust) → Real-people guidance content (Conversion). No current pillar or posting schedule connects these into one coherent candidate journey.</li>
    <li><b style="color:var(--ink)">Resources are allocated inversely to performance.</b> Life at VUS — the strongest awareness pillar — is under-invested at just 16.84% of posts, while Vietnam &amp; Relocation Support (underperforming across the board) and the "Generic Lifestyle" group still occupy a meaningful share of the posting schedule.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout">The problem isn't a lack of effective content — it's the <b>absence of a content architecture</b> that connects what's already proven to work into one coherent brand story, delivered to the right people at the right time.</div>
</section>

